text.tspan: Recall: A category is (co-)complete if it has all small (co-)limits.
Note. Can also be seen as a consequence of the adjoint functor theorem
i.e. if for every object X in C we have
an arrow from FX to GX, then we also
have a natural transformation from F
to G. Conversely, a nat tran from F
to G is also a nat tran with the same
functors restricted to the discrete cat.
* In particular, we have a (co-)cone with vertex c for a diagram D in
a poset P whenever are given arrows from c to each object in D.
* Also, to see that a poset is complete, it's enough to check it has all
limits on small, discrete index categories.
